<item>
            <title>[LU-12464] sanity test 51f still periodically runs out of memory with zfs backend</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12464</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Alex commented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9514&quot; title=&quot;sanity test 51f times out due to out of memory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9514&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9514&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that he still sees it too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For me client has 4G RAM and is a separate node so this should not really be happening.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s far from 100% but does happen from time to time nevertheless and apparently only on ZFS, so I am opening a separate ticket for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sample reports:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://testing.linuxhacker.ru:3333/lustre-reports/620/testresults/sanity-zfs-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://testing.linuxhacker.ru:3333/lustre-reports/620/testresults/sanity-zfs-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

